War finance and conflicts duration over time

# common palette for 04 (inside fill)
fill_pal <- c(
  "0" = "#fde0e0",
  "1" = "#f9bdbd",
  "2" = "#ef7d7d",
  "3" = "#c73838",
  "4" = "#891010"
)

# generic plotting function
plot_finance <- function(df, var, title, legend_title){
  df %>%
    filter(!is.na(.data[[var]])) %>%           # drop if variable missing
    ggplot(aes(x = start_year, y = duration,
               fill = factor(.data[[var]]))) +
    geom_jitter(width = 1, height = 0, size = 3,
                shape = 21, colour = "#660000",   # dark outline
                stroke = 0.6, alpha = 0.9) +
    scale_fill_manual(
      values = fill_pal,
      name = legend_title,
      labels = c("0 None","1 <25%","2 2550%","3 5075%","4 >75%")
    ) +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(floor(min(df$start_year)/10)*10,
                                    ceiling(max(df$start_year)/10)*10, by = 20)) +
    labs(x = "Duration of War Episodes",
         y = "Duration of War Episodes",
         title = title) +
    theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"))
}

p_debt   <- plot_finance(cwp_clean, "totalbrw",
                         "War Duration vs. Share Financed by Debt",
                         "Debt share")

p_abroad <- plot_finance(cwp_clean, "mnyabrd",
                         "War Duration vs. Share Financed from Abroad",
                         "Abroad share")

p_tax    <- plot_finance(cwp_clean, "domtax",
                         "War Duration vs. Share Financed by Taxation",
                         "Taxation share")

# palettes for two sources
reds  <- c("0"="#fde0e0","1"="#f9bdbd","2"="#ef7d7d","3"="#c73838","4"="#891010")
blues <- c("0"="#dce7f7","1"="#b8d1f5","2"="#6da3ea","3"="#357dd6","4"="#144a96")

# long form & drop NA levels
long_df <- cwp_clean %>%
  select(start_year, duration, domtax, mnyabrd) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(domtax, mnyabrd),
               names_to = "finance_type",
               values_to = "level") %>%
  filter(!is.na(level)) %>%
  mutate(
    finance_type = recode(finance_type,
                          domtax  = "Taxation",
                          mnyabrd = "From Abroad"),
    col_key = paste0(finance_type, "_", level)
  )

colour_map <- c(
  setNames(reds,  paste0("Taxation_",    names(reds))),
  setNames(blues, paste0("From Abroad_", names(blues)))
)

p_mix <- ggplot(long_df,
                aes(x = start_year,
                    y = duration,
                    fill = col_key)) +
  geom_jitter(width = 1, height = 0,
              shape = 21, colour = "black", stroke = 0.5,
              size = 3, alpha = 0.9) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = colour_map, guide = "none") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(floor(min(long_df$start_year)/10)*10,
                                  ceiling(max(long_df$start_year)/10)*10, by = 20)) +
  labs(
    x = "Year of War Outbreak",
    y = "Duration of War Episodes",
    title = "War Duration by Financing Source",
    subtitle = "Red = Domestic Sources, Blue = Sources from Abroad"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
        plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
# Map 04 ordinal codes to approximate shares (bin midpoints)
to_share <- function(x) case_when(
  x == 0 ~ 0.00,
  x == 1 ~ 0.125,  # <25%
  x == 2 ~ 0.375,  # 2550%
  x == 3 ~ 0.625,  # 5075%
  x == 4 ~ 0.875,  # >75%
  TRUE  ~ NA_real_
)

plot_df <- cwp_clean %>%
  mutate(
    tax_share    = to_share(domtax),
    abroad_share = to_share(mnyabrd),
    dom_share    = to_share(domwf),
    # Relative reliance index [0,1]: 0 = all domestic tax, 1 = all abroad
    R = case_when(
      is.na(tax_share) & is.na(abroad_share) ~ NA_real_,
      (tax_share + abroad_share) == 0        ~ NA_real_,   # or set to 0.5 neutral
      TRUE                                   ~ abroad_share / (tax_share + abroad_share)
    )
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(R))


# Plot with continuous bar (bottom=red, mid=grey, top=blue)
p_rel <- ggplot(plot_df, aes(x = start_year, y = duration)) +
  geom_jitter(aes(fill = R),
              shape = 21, colour = "black", stroke = 0.6,
              size = 3, alpha = 0.95,
              width = 0.5, height = 0.2) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "#7f0000", mid = "#999999", high = "#023e8a",
    midpoint = 0.5, limits = c(0,1),
    name = "Financing Mix",
    breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1),
    labels = c("Complete Domestic Taxation", "Balanced (50/50)", "Complete External Borrowing")
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(floor(min(plot_df$start_year)/10)*10,
                 ceiling(max(plot_df$start_year)/10)*10, by = 20)
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Year of War Outbreak",
    y = "Duration of War Episodes",
    title = "War Duration by Reliance on Borrowing"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
        legend.position = "right",
        legend.key.height = unit(3, "cm"),
        legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

War finance in crisis year

GCD <- read.csv("../data/GCD/20160923_global_crisis_data.csv")
cr_cols <- c("Banking.Crisis","Systemic.Crisis","Currency.Crises","Inflation.Crises")


GCD2 <- GCD %>%
  filter(Year >= 1816, Year <= 1913) %>%
  mutate(across(all_of(cr_cols), ~ as.integer(.x > 0)),
         any_crisis = as.integer(rowSums(across(all_of(cr_cols))) > 0))

crisis_year <- GCD2 %>%
  filter(Country == "United Kingdom", any_crisis == 1L) %>%
  arrange(Year)


df_GCD <- crisis_year %>%
  left_join(
    GCD2 %>%
      filter(Year %in% crisis_year$Year, any_crisis == 1L) %>%
      group_by(Year) %>%
      summarise(
        n_countries_any_crisis = n_distinct(Country),
        countries_in_crisis = paste(sort(unique(Country)), collapse = ", "),
        .groups = "drop"
      ),
    by = "Year"
  )
p_scatter_gcd <- ggplot(plot_df, aes(x = start_year, y = mnyabrd)) +
  geom_rect(
    data = df_GCD %>% mutate(Year = as.numeric(Year)),
    inherit.aes = FALSE,
    aes(xmin = Year - 0.5, xmax = Year + 0.5,
        ymin = -Inf, ymax = Inf),
    fill = "grey85", alpha = 0.5
  ) +
  geom_jitter(
    aes(fill = ifelse(mnyabrd >= 1, ">=25% External Sources", "<25% External Sources")),
    shape = 21, colour = "black", stroke = 0.5,
    width = 0.4, height = 0.2,
    size = 3, alpha = 0.9
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(">=25% External Sources" = "#1f77b4",
               "<25% External Sources"  = "#cbd5e8"),
    name = "War Finance"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(1816, 1913, by = 10),
    limits = c(1816, 1913)
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    breaks = 0:5,
    limits = c(-0.2, 4.2)
  ) +
  labs(
    x = "Year of War Outbreak",
    y = "Duration of War Episodes",
    title = "Reliance on External Financing in Wars (18161913)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
    legend.position = "right"
  )
